Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Comment:", "Subsubsection"],
 " Its turns out for up to five photon case, the symbolic solution to \
steady-state equations takes more than 5 minutes (I don\[CloseCurlyQuote]t \
know how many minutes it will take as the code was still running). Therefore, \
I followed the above method where I give all parameters except \
\[CapitalGamma] and then make a table of solutions for each \[CapitalGamma] \
value and use it to plot quantities of interest. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.734794347783555*^9, 3.7347943917263947`*^9}, {
  3.734803034190874*^9, 
  3.734803239126011*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"64be64c0-e65f-48e6-9d61-\
1de610b6807b"],

